				<description><![CDATA[If you're not really familiar with pepper then I suggest you move on to another post, but if you think you can handle the heat then enjoy!]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Today we&#8217;re taking it back to the motherland! Our dish for today is a traditional recipe from Nigeria called Pepper soup. Packed with protein and vitamins, it is sure to be a healthy alternative to so many meals!</p>



<p>The ingredients for this delicacy are:</p>



<ul><li> 2 Tsp Uziza leaves</li><li>1 Pound Goat meat</li><li>2 Tsp Crayfish</li><li>1 Tbs Pepper soup spice</li><li>1 Tsp Red Chili flakes</li><li>1 Tsp Ginger powder</li><li>1 Small Onion</li><li>1 Scotch bonnet minced</li><li>1 Seasoning cube</li><li>4 Cups Water </li></ul>



<p>Its time to get cooking, here are the instructions on how to make traditional Nigerian Pepper Soup:</p>



<ul><li>Cut the&nbsp;Goat meat into cutlets (see note 4). Then rinse thoroughly, transfer the meat into the Pot, add salt, Seasoning cube, habanero peppers&nbsp;and half of the Onion (see note 5) and cook for 30 minutes.</li><li>Add the pepper soup spice, red chili flakes, Ginger powder, the remaining grated onion, and crayfish. Leave it to cook for another 10 minutes.</li><li>Stir in the uziza leaves and let it simmer for another 5 minutes. Serve hot with Yam, Rice, Bread and more.</li></ul>



<p>Source:  <a href="https://cheflolaskitchen.com/african-pepper-soup/">https://cheflolaskitchen.com/african-pepper-soup/</a> </p>



